        {
          "username": "Lisa C",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "117294780992177393414",
          "user_review_count": 17,
          "user_photo_count": 2,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ33gbxMypucwmjyqZ84xVsmDWYwYUzi0Hicg8PsJRiLGY28Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "The doctor I have been seeing is great.  However, my issue is that Mount Sinai is committing fraud by upcoding services and charging patients absurd fees for minor procedures. I was given an estimate of nearly $7k for a cortisone injection.  When I looked more closely at the estimate, it showed that the total estimated charges were actually closer to $2k, but I would owe close to $7k.  I\u2019m assuming they were just going to pocket my money for no reason?  Of course, I can\u2019t speak with anyone about this because I keep getting transferred from one department to another on the phone, but everyone says it\u2019s not their problem.  Now I have to find a new provider because of the shady billing practices.  If you\u2019re thinking of seeing any provider through Mount Sinai, I would definitely look elsewhere if you don\u2019t want to be scammed.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tWSWJsUkRlR1l5V1docmQzWkVaR2htTkhoVVpHYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x653199a7b6323431!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkVIblRDeGYyWWhrd3ZEZGhmNHhUZGc%7C%7C?hl=en",
